    "body": "### Problem\n\nNvim crashes on assertion added in ad8bce6674965c980b595f05c3eb7b49cb64e50d when starts with `vsplit` command. \n\n```\nsrc/nvim/decoration.c:868: decor_conceal_line: Assertion `row >= 0' failed.\n```\n```cpp\n#0  __pthread_kill_implementation (threadid=<optimized out>, signo=signo@entry=6, no_tid=no_tid@entry=0) at ./nptl/pthread_kill.c:44\n#1  0x00007fb789f669ff in __pthread_kill_internal (threadid=<optimized out>, signo=6) at ./nptl/pthread_kill.c:89\n#2  0x00007fb789f11cc2 in __GI_raise (sig=sig@entry=6) at ../sysdeps/posix/raise.c:26\n#3  0x00007fb789efa4ac in __GI_abort () at ./stdlib/abort.c:73\n#4  0x00007fb789efa420 in __assert_fail_base (fmt=<optimized out>, assertion=<optimized out>, file=<optimized out>, line=868, function=<optimized out>) at ./assert/assert.c:118\n#5  0x00007fb789f0a6dc in __assert_fail (assertion=<optimized out>, file=<optimized out>, line=<optimized out>, function=<optimized out>) at ./assert/assert.c:127\n#6  0x000056405fc17774 in decor_conceal_line (wp=<optimized out>, row=<optimized out>, check_cursor=<optimized out>) at .../src/nvim/decoration.c:868\n#7  0x000056405fe710bb in plines_win_full (wp=0x564072c138d0, lnum=<optimized out>, nextp=<optimized out>, foldedp=<optimized out>, cache=<optimized out>, limit_winheight=true) at .../src/nvim/plines.c:901\n#8  0x000056405fe24f9d in curs_rows (wp=0x564072c138d0) at .../src/nvim/move.c:701\n#9  curs_columns (wp=0x564072c138d0, may_scroll=1) at .../src/nvim/move.c:811\n#10 0x000056405ff823d4 in win_set_inner_size (wp=0x564072c138d0, valid_cursor=<optimized out>) at .../src/nvim/window.c:6760\n#11 0x000056405ff739e7 in win_new_width (wp=0x564072c138d0, width=<optimized out>) at .../src/nvim/window.c:6790\n#12 win_split_ins (size=size@entry=0, flags=2, new_wp=new_wp@entry=0x0, dir=dir@entry=0, to_flatten=to_flatten@entry=0x0) at .../src/nvim/window.c:1450\n#13 0x000056405ff76150 in win_split (size=0, flags=<optimized out>) at .../src/nvim/window.c:1060\n#14 0x000056405fd402ce in ex_splitview (eap=0x7ffc2b3cc240) at .../src/nvim/ex_docmd.c:5473\n#15 0x000056405fd33e45 in execute_cmd0 (retv=retv@entry=0x7ffc2b3cc1a4, eap=eap@entry=0x7ffc2b3cc240, errormsg=errormsg@entry=0x7ffc2b3cc1b8, preview=preview@entry=false) at .../src/nvim/ex_docmd.c:1734\n#16 0x000056405fd39575 in do_one_cmd (cmdlinep=0x7ffc2b3cc1b0, flags=11, cstack=0x7ffc2b3cc400, fgetline=0x0, cookie=0x0) at .../src/nvim/ex_docmd.c:2364\n#17 do_cmdline (cmdline=<optimized out>, fgetline=<optimized out>, cookie=<optimized out>, flags=<optimized out>) at .../src/nvim/ex_docmd.c:677\n#18 0x000056405fc2067c in do_cmdline_cmd (cmd=<optimized out>) at .../src/nvim/ex_docmd.c:375\n#19 exe_commands (parmp=0x7ffc2b3ccb20) at .../src/nvim/main.c:1947\n#20 main (argc=<optimized out>, argv=<optimized out>) at .../src/nvim/main.c:587\n```\nCc: @luukvbaal \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean -c vs`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo crash\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1407+gfafc329bbd\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
